         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne, 16th June 1890 ¶ Sir ¶  ¶ I have the honor to request, that you please to alter the Estimates for my branch for 1890/91, submitted by me on 10th April, ¶ See M to T. Wilson, 10 April 1890. ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">90.06.16</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Thomas Wilson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">P90/4250, unit 513, VPRS 3992/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style=""/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS written by G. Luehmann and signed by M.</p>
               </note>Melbourne, 16th June 1890</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the honor to request, that you please to alter the Estimates for my branch for 1890/91, submitted by me on 10th April,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to T. Wilson, 10 April 1890. On 18 April 1890,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>G. Luehmann sent a telegram, now in the same file,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to J. Killen at the Chief Secretary's Office:<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>'Eighteen pounds deducted from salary of fifth class clerk for quarters'.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in regard to the salary of the 5th Class Clerk, which was erroneously put down at £182.-<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>instead of £200.-<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The error arose through £18 having been deducted for rent, for which extra services are rendered. The same officer would also be entitled to an additional sum of £15.-<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for salary during 1889/90, deducted through the same error, and I would solicit that this amount be placed on the Supplemental Estimates.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation dated 18 June 1890: 'Baron Von Mueller will write again if he still wishes the suggestion herein carried out Saw Mr Luehmann'.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On 16 June 1890,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Luehmann wrote to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Killen: 'I shall be very thankful if you can still alter the salary of Mr Renner, 5th Class Clerk, from £182 to £200.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I was always under the impression that £18 had been charged to him for rent of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>a<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>room, but find now that this sum had been added to his salary in 1885/6, when he had to pay it back monthly. In 1886/7 this arrangement ceased and he only got an increment of £2.-<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>In 1888/9 he got [<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">obscured in p/c</seg>] £177 In 1889/90 £182, [<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">obscured in p/c</seg>] should have had £1[<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">4?? obscured in p/c</seg>] therefore £15 are d[ue] to him for arrears.'</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your most obedient servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Govt. Botanist</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">T. R. Wilson Esq</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Under Secretary</p>
         </div>
